## Part III: Prophecies Concerning World Empires

### A. Nebuchadnezzar's Image — Four Kingdoms

**The Prophecy (Characteristics Given):**

**Daniel 2:31-40** — *"This image's head was of fine gold, his breast and his arms of silver, his belly and his thighs of brass, His legs of iron... Thou art this head of gold. And after thee shall arise another kingdom inferior to thee, and another third kingdom of brass, which shall bear rule over all the earth. And the fourth kingdom shall be strong as iron."*

| Characteristic Given | Material | Meaning |
|---------------------|----------|---------|
| First kingdom | Head of gold | "Thou art this head of gold" — ruling at that time |
| Second kingdom | Breast/arms of silver | "Inferior" to the first |
| Third kingdom | Belly/thighs of brass | "Bear rule over all the earth" |
| Fourth kingdom | Legs of iron | "Strong as iron... breaketh in pieces" |
| Division | Feet of iron and clay | "Kingdom shall be divided" |

**The Fulfillment (Names Revealed):**

| Characteristic | Fulfillment | Historical Names |
|---------------|-------------|-----------------|
| Head of gold | Ruling empire when prophecy given | **Babylon** under **Nebuchadnezzar** |
| Breast/arms of silver | Conquered Babylon 539 BC | **Medo-Persia** under **Cyrus** (two arms = two peoples) |
| Belly/thighs of brass | Conquered Persia 331 BC | **Greece** under **Alexander the Great** |
| Legs of iron | Conquered Greece | **Rome** — iron monarchy, crushing power |
| Feet of iron/clay | Rome's division | **Ten barbarian kingdoms** of Europe |

**Scripture confirms the succession:**

**Daniel 5:28** — *"PERES; Thy kingdom is divided, and given to the Medes and Persians."* (Babylon → Medo-Persia)

**Daniel 8:20-21** — *"The ram which thou sawest having two horns are the kings of Media and Persia. And the rough goat is the king of Grecia."* (Medo-Persia → Greece)

